                <MainParagraph>The National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA),
                                    formerly the National Imagery and Mapping Agency, was
                                    established in 1996 and is under the authority, direction, and
                                    control of the Under Secretary of Defense for Intelligence. NGA
                                    is a DOD combat support agency and a member of the national
                                    intelligence community. NGA's mission is to provide timely,
                                    relevant, and accurate geospatial intelligence in support of our
                                    national security. Geospatial intelligence means the use and
                                    analysis of imagery to describe, assess, and visually depict
                                    physical features and geographically referenced activities on
                                    the Earth. Headquartered in Bethesda, MD, NGA has major
                                    facilities in the Washington, DC, Northern Virginia, and St.
                                    Louis, MO, areas with NGA support teams
                                    worldwide.</MainParagraph>
